abstract: The dismantling of the protest camp under HSBC’s Asia headquarters ends the last vestiges of what was once a global movement.
snippet: The dismantling of the protest camp under HSBC’s Asia headquarters ends the last vestiges of what was once a global movement.
lead_paragraph: HONG KONG  — Court officers and the police shut down the 306-day-old Occupy Hong Kong protest Tuesday in the street-level plaza under HSBC’s Asia headquarters, spending six hours in a sometimes disorderly confrontation that ended with the removal of the dozen protesters and the seizure of their tents and other possessions.

headline.main: Occupy Hong Kong Protesters Forcibly Removed
headline.print_headline: Eviction of Occupy Protesters Begins at Site in Hong Kong
